    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Feb. 17<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1882</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I hope that you will express to your fellow-students my thanks for their kind good wishes on my birth-day. I sincerely, hope that you may all be successful in your several careers, &amp; all fairly happy.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Believe me | Yours faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13678.xml">letter from Max Steffen, 12 February 1882</ref>. CD’s birthday was 12 February; he was 73.</note> 
        </div>
    
